720151f-a.title: Manhattan: Greenwich Avenue - 10th Street
720151f-a.text:
Greenwich Ave, west side, north from and including the S.W. corner of 10th Street, to but not including Charles Street. This view also shows 10th Street, north side, from but not including Patchin Place, to and including Greenwich Ave, The excavation in the foreground is for the new municipal women's jail on the site of old Jefferson Market
Courts.
December 14, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

711048f-b.title: Manhattan: 10th Street - Greenwich Avenue
711048f-b.text:
10th Street (formerly Amos Street), east from and including Greenwich Avenue, showing the Jefferson Market Courthouse and clock tower (1875) on the S.W. corner of Sixth Avenue, and the Cushman Bakery on the N.E. conner of Greenwich Avenue. This branch of the Cushman chain is the original Cushman store, established in this
building in 1854.
The car track in the foreground is the westbound track of the 8th
Street crosstown surface line.
March 29, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
